The paper deals with visuomotor control, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) that focuses on controlling robotic systems using visual feedback. The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for processing raw image observations. The proposed approach involves learning the controller and its conditioning in an end-to-end manner, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also deals with system-level issues such as deployability and planning horizon, which are relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
